Package college

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ACTScores
    represents a set of ACT scores, which includes writing/English/math/cumulative scores only the cumulative score is currently used to calculate admission chances because some colleges does not have stats for all aspects
    AnnualStats
    represents the test score statistics for one year of a specified college
    ChanceCalculator
    code to calculate admission chances
    GPACalc
    This represents a GPA Calculator with methods to calculator weighted/unweighted GPA and grades
    SATScores
    represents a set of SAT scores with critical reading/writing/math/total aspects only total is used to determine admission chances because some colleges does not provide all relevant information.
    School
    a college entity that is pulled from online JSON library
    Search
    represents the entities after the "search" button is pressed includes JSON parsing and organizes data into objects
    SearchFunction
    representing the entities being added whenever the search college button is pressed
